Hi Tim,

I see jvmver= "1.6.0" for a JDK build dated January 5, 2006.  I experimented with adding:

    else if (jvmver.startsWith("1.6"))
        rcv = RuntimeManager.getRuntimeComponentType("standard.jre").getVersion("6.0");

Then duplicating extension point declarations for "6.0".  Eventually ran into JavaFacetUtils.setCompilerLevel() which uses org.eclipse.jdt.core.JavaCore.VERSION_1_5, which has no 1.6 version constant.  Maybe JDT isn't ready for 6.0/1.6 yet.

Larry
